1. Important: Delete the existing venv folder before doing all the steps below.
2. Extensions view or Ctrl+Shift+X
3. Search for "Python" and install the extension by Microsoft.
4. Open the project folder.
5. Run terminal, Ctrl+Shift+`
6. Create virtual environment: python -m venv venv
7. Run this in terminal: .\venv\Scripts\activate

8. Select the Python Interpreter in VS Code:
- Press Ctrl+Shift+P to open the Command Palette.
- Type Python: Select Interpreter and select it.
- In the list of interpreters, choose the one that points to the venv folder (it will look like ./venv/Scripts/python.exe on Windows.

9. Run this in terminal (installing necessary libraries);
- dazz- for faster process of installing necessary libraries
  - make sure to have the new file: pythonrequirements.txt
  - for react libararies: open terminal, just run "npm install"
  - for python libararies: open another terminal, run "pip install -r pythonrequirements.txt"

- npm install react react-dom
- npm install axios
- npm install react-router-dom
- npm install recharts
- npm install html2pdf.js
- pip install fastapi
- pip install uvicorn
- pip install pydantic
- pip install python-jose
- pip install passlib[bcrypt]
- pip install pymongo
- pip install python-dotenv
- pip install python-multipart
- pip install Pillow
- pip install pydantic[email]
- pip install email-validator
- pip install bcrypt==3.2.2
- pip install pandas openpyxl xlrd
- pip install numpy scipy statsmodels python-dateutil pandas

10. Put the backend files on venv.

DATABASE CONNECTION: @etil @yel - palagay tutorial ty

Running the project:
1. Backend (main.py under venv)
- uvicorn main:app --reload or python main.py

2. Frontend (index.js)
- npm start
